<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>First administrator — CMS</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; max-width: 28rem; margin: 3rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; }
    label { display: block; margin-top: 1rem; }
    input { width: 100%; padding: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.25rem; box-sizing: border-box; }
    button { margin-top: 1.5rem; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; }
    .err { color: #b00; margin-top: 1rem; }
    .hint { color: #444; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>First administrator</h1>
  <p>The <code>ADMINS</code> environment variable has no users. Create the first administrator — only an argon2 password hash will be written to <code>.env</code>.</p>
  {% if error %}<p class="err">{{ error }}</p>{% endif %}
  <form method="post" action="/cms/login">
    <label>Email <input name="user_email" type="email" required autocomplete="username"></label>
    <label>Password <input name="password" type="password" required minlength="8" autocomplete="new-password"></label>
    <p class="hint">After saving, restart the application (for example <code>systemctl restart …</code>) so settings reload and the user is imported into the database.</p>
    <button type="submit">Save to .env</button>
  </form>
</body>
</html>
